  <para style="p">
    <verse number="9" style="v" sid="SNG 5:9" />¶ What <char style="add">is</char> thy <char style="w" strong="H1730">beloved</char> more than <char style="add">another</char> <char style="w" strong="H1730">beloved</char>, O thou <char style="w" strong="H3303">fairest</char> among <char style="w" strong="H0802">women</char>? what <char style="add">is</char> thy <char style="w" strong="H1730">beloved</char> more than <char style="add">another</char> <char style="w" strong="H1730">beloved</char>, that <char style="w" strong="H3602">thou</char> dost so <char style="w" strong="H7650">charge</char> us? <verse eid="SNG 5:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="SNG 5:10" />My <char style="w" strong="H1730">beloved</char> <char style="add">is</char> <char style="w" strong="H6703">white</char> and <char style="w" strong="H0122">ruddy</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H1713">chiefest</char> among ten <char style="w" strong="H7233">thousand</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">the chiefest: Heb. a standard-bearer</char></note> <verse eid="SNG 5:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="SNG 5:11" />His <char style="w" strong="H7218">head</char> <char style="add">is as</char> the <char style="w" strong="H3800">most</char> fine <char style="w" strong="H6337">gold</char>, his <char style="w" strong="H6977">locks</char> <char style="add">are</char> <char style="w" strong="H8534">bushy</char>, <char style="add">and</char> <char style="w" strong="H7838">black</char> as a <char style="w" strong="H6158">raven</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.11 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">bushy: or, curled</char></note> <verse eid="SNG 5:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="SNG 5:12" />His <char style="w" strong="H5869">eyes</char> <char style="add">are</char> as <char style="add">the eyes</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3123">doves</char> by the <char style="w" strong="H0650">riv